494
00:36:10.135 --> 00:36:12.137
I always had
a distaste for science.

495
00:36:12.221 --> 00:36:14.181
Well. maybe you had
a bad teacher.

496
00:36:14.264 --> 00:36:16.599
Yeah. Ms. Ratliff
was a piece of work.

497
00:36:16.684 --> 00:36:19.311
Ratliff?
You bet.

498
00:36:19.394 --> 00:36:21.563
She's still kicking around.
believe it or not.

499
00:36:21.646 --> 00:36:25.442
Oh. I believe it.
Mummies never die. so they tell me.

500
00:36:26.068 --> 00:36:27.568
Sarah. my daughter...

501
00:36:28.945 --> 00:36:33.117
Galaxies. the universe. whatnot...
She always understood all that stuff.

502
00:36:33.199 --> 00:36:35.661
I always figured there was enough
going on down here.

503
00:36:35.744 --> 00:36:37.496
I never needed to look elsewhere.

504
00:36:38.038 --> 00:36:39.789
Your daughter.
what grade is she?

505
00:36:39.873 --> 00:36:42.668
- Maybe I'll get her in my class.
- No. she. uh...

506
00:36:42.751 --> 00:36:45.295
She lives with her mom in the city.

507
00:36:45.378 --> 00:36:48.840
Thanks for coming out. Teach.
We really appreciate it.

508
00:36:51.050 --> 00:36:53.929
- She died a few years back.
- Sorry?

509
00:36:54.012 --> 00:36:55.264
His kid.

510
00:37:07.735 --> 00:37:09.277
Lucas. do you copy?
It's Mike.

511
00:37:09.360 --> 00:37:12.197
<i>- Lucas?</i>
- Hey. it's Lucas.

512
00:37:12.280 --> 00:37:13.282
I know it's you.

513
00:37:13.364 --> 00:37:16.534
And say "over" when you're done talking
so I know when you're done. Over.

514
00:37:16.617 --> 00:37:18.244
I'm done. Over.

515
00:37:18.327 --> 00:37:20.748
I'm worried about Will. Over.

516
00:37:20.831 --> 00:37:22.875
Yeah.

517
00:37:24.710 --> 00:37:26.628
This is crazy. Over.

518
00:37:26.711 --> 00:37:28.338
I was thinking...

519
00:37:29.840 --> 00:37:32.675
Will could've cast Protection last night.
but he didn't.

520
00:37:32.760 --> 00:37:33.760
He cast Fireball.

521
00:37:33.844 --> 00:37:37.597
<i>- Over.</i>
- What's your point? Over.

522
00:37:37.681 --> 00:37:42.393
My point is... he could've played it safe.
but he didn't.

523
00:37:42.478 --> 00:37:44.353
He put himself in danger
to help the party.

524
00:37:44.438 --> 00:37:45.563
<i>Over.</i>

525
00:37:48.358 --> 00:37:50.777
Meet me in ten.
Over and out.

526
00:38:21.599 --> 00:38:22.601
What are you doing here?

527
00:38:22.684 --> 00:38:24.978
I told you on the phone.
I'm under house arrest now.

528
00:38:25.061 --> 00:38:27.898
- I figured we'd just study here.
- No. No way.

529
00:38:27.981 --> 00:38:30.233
Oh. come on.
I can't have you failing this test.

530
00:38:30.317 --> 00:38:32.110
So just... bear with me.

531
00:38:35.155 --> 00:38:36.155
What'd I tell you?

532
00:38:37.574 --> 00:38:38.699
Ninja.

533
00:38:52.755 --> 00:38:54.215
You like that ice cream. huh?

534
00:38:55.467 --> 00:38:56.885
Smile looks good on you.

535
00:38:57.719 --> 00:38:59.304
You know. smile?

536
00:39:08.313 --> 00:39:10.065
All right.
You just sit tight.

537
00:39:10.148 --> 00:39:13.527
Whoever it is. I'll tell 'em to go away
real quick. all right?

538
00:39:15.737 --> 00:39:18.407
Yeah. yeah. yeah...

539
00:39:19.532 --> 00:39:22.034
- Hey. can I help you?
- Hi. you must be Benny Hammond.

540
00:39:22.119 --> 00:39:24.371
I'm afraid I am. I'm afraid
we're closed for the evening. too.

541
00:39:24.454 --> 00:39:27.206
- So try back tomorrow morning.
- Connie Frazier. Social Services.

542
00:39:27.291 --> 00:39:30.168
Ah. Social Services. My apologies.
I didn't expect you so soon.

543
00:39:30.251 --> 00:39:33.088
- That's a heck of a drive.
- Not too bad this time of night.

544
00:39:33.172 --> 00:39:35.423
Hey. listen. I...
I haven't told her that you're coming yet.

545
00:39:35.507 --> 00:39:39.469
I didn't want her running off again.
She's a tad skittish.

546
00:39:39.552 --> 00:39:42.181
- Children I work with usually are.
- Right. right.

547
00:39:42.764 --> 00:39:45.601
- So. where is she?
- Right. She's in the kitchen.

548
00:39:45.684 --> 00:39:47.518
- Come on up. I'll introduce you.
- Thank you.

549
00:39:47.603 --> 00:39:49.396
Sorry again for trying
to turn you away there.

550
00:39:49.478 --> 00:39:50.521
- It's fine.
- You know. it's funny.

551
00:39:50.606 --> 00:39:53.025
Your. uh. voice sounds different on the...

552
00:40:23.847 --> 00:40:26.766
Ah. man.
This is it.

553
00:40:35.525 --> 00:40:37.360
Hey. guys.
You feel that?

554
00:40:40.405 --> 00:40:42.074
- I think maybe we should go back.
- No.

555
00:40:42.157 --> 00:40:44.784
We're not going back.
Just stay close.

556
00:40:44.867 --> 00:40:45.994
Come on.

557
00:40:47.119 --> 00:40:50.456
Just stay on channel six.
Don't do anything stupid.

558
00:40:55.128 --> 00:40:56.463
Hey. guys. wait up.

559
00:40:57.005 --> 00:40:58.422
Wait up!

560
00:41:04.304 --> 00:41:07.099
"Which polymers occur naturally?"

561
00:41:08.516 --> 00:41:10.978
Starch and cellulose.

562
00:41:11.061 --> 00:41:12.311
Mmm.

563
00:41:12.396 --> 00:41:16.650
"In a molecule of CH4.
the hydrogen atoms are spatially oriented

564
00:41:16.733 --> 00:41:19.193
- towards the centers of..."
- Tetrahedrons.

565
00:41:19.277 --> 00:41:21.780
Wow.
Jesus. how many of these did you make?

566
00:41:21.862 --> 00:41:23.699
You said you wanted to help.

567
00:41:24.740 --> 00:41:25.951
How about this? How about...

568
00:41:26.034 --> 00:41:27.577
How about every time
that you get something right.

569
00:41:27.661 --> 00:41:29.161
I have to take off
an item of clothing.

570
00:41:29.246 --> 00:41:30.831
But every time
that you get something wrong...

571
00:41:30.914 --> 00:41:32.123
- Uh. pass.
- Oh. come on.

572
00:41:32.206 --> 00:41:33.250
- Come on.
- No.

573
00:41:33.333 --> 00:41:34.710
- Come on. It'll be fun.
- No.

574
00:41:34.793 --> 00:41:36.168
"During fractional distillation.

575
00:41:36.253 --> 00:41:38.922
hydrocarbons are separated
according to their..."

576
00:41:39.005 --> 00:41:40.047
Melting point.

577
00:41:41.507 --> 00:41:43.677
Ooh. it's boiling points.

578
00:41:43.760 --> 00:41:45.177
That's what I meant.

579
00:41:45.262 --> 00:41:47.264
Yeah. that's not what you said.

580
00:41:48.181 --> 00:41:49.974
- No.
- No?

581
00:41:50.851 --> 00:41:53.186
Oh. do you need...
Do you need help. or...

582
00:41:53.269 --> 00:41:54.313
No.

583
00:42:15.833 --> 00:42:17.460
Steve.
Steve. come on.

584
00:42:17.543 --> 00:42:18.545
What?

585
00:42:18.628 --> 00:42:20.755
Are you crazy?
My parents are here.

586
00:42:22.465 --> 00:42:24.967
That's weird. I... don't see them.

587
00:42:28.804 --> 00:42:33.476
Was this your plan all along?
To... to get in my room and then...

588
00:42:33.559 --> 00:42:36.146
- get another notch on your belt.
- No. Nancy. no.

589
00:42:36.228 --> 00:42:38.356
I'm not Laurie. or Amy. or Becky.

590
00:42:38.440 --> 00:42:40.025
You mean. you're not a slut.

591
00:42:40.858 --> 00:42:41.943
That's not what I'm saying.

592
00:42:42.027 --> 00:42:43.778
You know. you're so cute when you lie.

593
00:42:44.278 --> 00:42:45.530
Shut up.

594
00:42:48.407 --> 00:42:49.784
Bad Steve.

595
00:42:49.867 --> 00:42:53.413
Bad.
Don't do that to Miss Nancy...

596
00:42:53.996 --> 00:42:56.041
You're an idiot. Steve Harrington.

597
00:42:56.958 --> 00:42:59.001
You are beautiful. Nancy Wheeler.

598
00:43:05.425 --> 00:43:08.010
"Compared to the rate
of inorganic reactions.

599
00:43:08.094 --> 00:43:11.847
the rate of organic reactions
is generally..."

600
00:43:14.851 --> 00:43:17.896
Jonathan. wow.
You took these?

601
00:43:18.813 --> 00:43:20.315
These are great.

602
00:43:21.440 --> 00:43:24.402
Wow. they really are.

603
00:43:25.570 --> 00:43:28.657
- I know I haven't been there for you.
- I've been...

604
00:43:28.739 --> 00:43:30.826
working so hard and I...

605
00:43:30.909 --> 00:43:32.744
I just feel bad.
I don't even...

606
00:43:32.827 --> 00:43:35.288
barely know what's going on with you.

607
00:43:35.371 --> 00:43:38.125
All right?
I am sorry about that.

608
00:43:41.503 --> 00:43:42.795
Hey. what is it?

609
00:43:43.713 --> 00:43:45.047
What is it. honey?

610
00:43:46.800 --> 00:43:49.219
- Nothing.
- Tell me. Tell me.

611
00:43:49.302 --> 00:43:51.346
- Come on. You can...
- No.

612
00:43:51.429 --> 00:43:52.597
It's just...

613
00:43:53.806 --> 00:43:55.599
I should've been there for him.

614
00:43:55.684 --> 00:43:58.686
No. Oh. no.
You can't do that to yourself.

615
00:43:58.769 --> 00:44:01.981
This was not your fault.
Do you hear me?

616
00:44:02.065 --> 00:44:05.735
- He is... close.
- I know it. I...

617
00:44:06.402 --> 00:44:09.114
I feel it in my heart.

618
00:44:09.864 --> 00:44:12.659
You just have to...
You have to trust me on this. okay?

619
00:44:15.411 --> 00:44:17.079
- Yeah.
- Oh. look at this.

620
00:44:17.164 --> 00:44:19.541
Look at this one.
Look at this one.

621
00:44:21.876 --> 00:44:24.045
- I mean. that's it. right?
- Yeah.

622
00:44:24.128 --> 00:44:25.922
That's it.
That's the one.

623
00:44:29.509 --> 00:44:32.429
Hello?

624
00:44:32.512 --> 00:44:34.139
Hello?

625
00:44:34.222 --> 00:44:35.264
Lonnie?

626
00:44:35.347 --> 00:44:37.099
- Dad?
- Hopper?

627
00:44:37.184 --> 00:44:39.226
Who is this?

628
00:44:42.521 --> 00:44:43.565
Will?

629
00:44:44.440 --> 00:44:45.525
- Will?
- It's Will?

630
00:44:48.360 --> 00:44:49.737
Mom. it's Will?

631
00:44:50.739 --> 00:44:52.157
Who is this?

632
00:44:52.239 --> 00:44:54.367
- What have you done to my boy?
- What? What?

633
00:44:54.451 --> 00:44:55.952
Give me back my son!

634
00:44:57.913 --> 00:44:59.748
Hello?

635
00:44:59.831 --> 00:45:01.081
Hello. who is this?

636
00:45:01.166 --> 00:45:03.918
Hello? Who is this?

637
00:45:04.001 --> 00:45:06.463
Mom. who was it? Who was it. Mom?

638
00:45:06.545 --> 00:45:08.215
- It was him.
- Look at me. Mom. Was it Will?

639
00:45:08.297 --> 00:45:09.507
- Yes.
- What did he say?

640
00:45:09.590 --> 00:45:11.717
He just breathed.
He just breathed.

641
00:45:11.800 --> 00:45:13.762
- And was someone else there?
- I...

642
00:45:13.844 --> 00:45:16.556
- Mom. who was there? Who was it?
- It was him.

643
00:45:16.639 --> 00:45:19.351
I know it was his breathing.
I know it was his breathing.

644
00:45:20.643 --> 00:45:22.019
Will!

645
00:45:23.021 --> 00:45:25.523
- Will!
- Byers!

646
00:45:25.606 --> 00:45:28.360
I've got your <i>X-Men 134!</i>

647
00:45:29.110 --> 00:45:31.195
Guys. I really think
we should turn back.

648
00:45:31.278 --> 00:45:32.530
Seriously. Dustin?

649
00:45:32.614 --> 00:45:34.907
You wanna be a baby.
then go home already!

650
00:45:34.990 --> 00:45:36.701
I'm just being realistic. Lucas!

651
00:45:36.784 --> 00:45:38.786
No. you're just being a big sissy!

652
00:45:39.411 --> 00:45:42.791
Did you ever think Will went
missing because he ran into something bad?

653
00:45:42.873 --> 00:45:45.751
And we're going to the exact same spot
where he was last seen?

654
00:45:45.835 --> 00:45:48.672
- And we have no weapons or anything?
- Dustin. shut up.

655
00:45:48.755 --> 00:45:50.757
I'm just saying.
does that seem smart to you?

656
00:45:50.840 --> 00:45:52.967
Shut up. Shut up.

657
00:45:53.050 --> 00:45:54.719
Did you guys hear that?
